_:cc3830c1ce8793ef3ab08d3a6bb659c6 a <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E52_Time-span> ;
	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "He was  a saint  and martyr venerated in the Byzantine empire  and all over the Christian Orient, especially in \n                        Egypt. He was supposedly martyred during the Diocletian\n                        persecution of Christians  in Kotyaion. Minās seems to have been a popular saint in \n                        Ethiopia to which both his frequent representations in art as well as the name of 16th century \n               \n                           \n                     ʾaṣeMinās, named after him, testify.\n                     " .
